        <p class="lede-p">If you run a small business under $5M in revenue, you do not have the bandwidth to do SEO yourself. <strong>Done-for-you services</strong> hand the entire process — keyword research, content, on-page, links, reporting — to someone else. The catch: pricing ranges from $49/mo to $5,000+/mo, and most "guides" online are paid placement.</p>

        <p>We tested 8 of the most-recommended services over the last 90 days, on real small-business sites in HVAC, dental, e-commerce, and SaaS. Here is the honest ranking, the pricing tiers explained, and a 9-point checklist so you do not get burned.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-tldr">
          <div class="callout-label">⚡ TL;DR — Pick by budget</div>
          <p><strong>Under $200/mo:</strong> theStacc ($49) bundles content + GBP + ranks. The only true done-for-you platform at this price. <strong>$500–$2,000/mo:</strong> Searchbloom or BrightLocal — productised agencies that ship monthly deliverables. <strong>$2,500+/mo:</strong> Victorious or WebFX for full-service strategy + custom content.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is a "done-for-you" SEO service?</h2>
        <p>"Done-for-you SEO" (DFY SEO) means a service handles the entire SEO function for you, from strategy to publishing to reporting. Unlike consultants (who advise) or in-house (which you hire), DFY services own the work end-to-end and charge a monthly fee.</p>

        <p>There are three distinct flavours in 2026:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>Productised platforms</strong> — software-driven, $49–$199/mo (theStacc, BrightLocal). Best for under-$1M businesses that want predictable output.</li>
          <li><strong>Productised agencies</strong> — humans + templates, $500–$2,500/mo (Searchbloom, Loganix). Best for $1–5M businesses that need light customisation.</li>
          <li><strong>Full-service agencies</strong> — custom strategy + dedicated team, $2,500+/mo (Victorious, WebFX, Ignite Visibility). Best for $5M+ businesses with budget and competitive niches.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">⚠️ Watch for these red flags</div>
          <p>Avoid any agency that <strong>(a)</strong> guarantees specific rankings in 30 days, <strong>(b)</strong> requires a 12-month contract without a 90-day exit clause, or <strong>(c)</strong> charges less than $500/mo for "custom" work — that math does not pencil out. You are paying for templates and a name.</p>
        </div>

